-- FTSE 100 Index Is Little Changed; Rio Tinto, HSBC, BHP Billiton Decline
-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 2010-10-29T08:30:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-29/ftse-100-index-is-little-changed-rio-tinto-hsbc-bhp-billiton-decline.html
U.K. stocks decline, led by a
retreat in mining companies and British Airways Plc.  The FTSE 100 Index lost 0.2 percent to 5,664.99 at 9:26
a.m. in London.  Xstrata Plc, Rio Tinto Group and Antofagasta Plc all lost
more than 1 percent. British Airways, which reported results
today, fell 3 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sarah Jones at 
 sjones35@bloomberg.net  